# Update Topic Index

When creating a **new** research note (`.md` file) inside any domain folder (`01-*` through `11-*`), you MUST append a row to the **Topic Index** table in `README.md`.

## Format

```
| <next #> | [<H1 title from new file>](./<relative-path>) | <Domain> | `tag1`, `tag2` |
```

- `#` — increment from the last row number
- Title — use the exact `# H1` heading from the new file
- Domain — map folder prefix to domain name (see table below)
- Tags — add 2–3 lowercase, hyphenated keywords relevant to the topic

## Domain Map

| Folder prefix | Domain |
|---------------|--------|
| 01-* | Fundamentals |
| 02-* | System Design |
| 03-* | Languages |
| 04-* | Frontend |
| 05-* | Backend |
| 06-* | DevOps & Infra |
| 07-* | Databases |
| 08-* | Security |
| 09-* | Testing |
| 10-* | Soft Skills |
| 11-* | AI/ML |

## When creating a playground experiment

Append a row to the **Playground experiments** table instead:

```
| <next #> | [<Title>](./playground/<folder>/SUMMARY.md) | <Short description> |
```

## When deleting a note

Remove the corresponding row and re-number subsequent rows.

## Rebuild from scratch

Run `bash scripts/update-topic-index.sh` to regenerate the full index from the file system. Tags will be left empty for manual review.
